classes.components

Class Pair<F,S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • classes.components.Pair<F,S>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PairInterface, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Pair<F,S>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PairInterface, java.lang.Cloneable
    Container to ease passing around a tuple of two objects. This object provides a sensible implementation of equals(), returning true if equals() is true on each of the contained objects. This object is generic and is intended to be immutable.
    Author:
    Abraham Mubanzo
